        .section__content
          %h3.h3 I'm kind of new here, but not really.
          %p After 10 years working as a UX developer on world class products and with global clients, I've made the transition into a role focused primarily on product, UX and interaction design. Don't worry, writing code and building beautiful interfaces still makes me feel like a magnificent hybrid of <a href="http://www.theresacaputo.com/" target="_blank" title="Theresa Caputo">Theresa Caputo's hair</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iris_Kyle" target="_blank" title="Iris Kyle">Iris Kyle</a>.
          %p Before making this transition, I was working with the fine folks over at <a href="http://www.format.com/" target="_blank" title="Format">Format.com</a>, and before that, I was building epic sh!t at <a href="http://teehanlax.com/" tite="Teehan+Lax" target="_blank">Teehan+Lax</a>.
          %p Over the span of my 10+ year career, I’ve had the pleasure of working with some major brands like Google, Starbucks, Stella Artois, Honda, KFC, and Bell, and also with some incredible local Toronto brands like The Black Hoof and Bar Isabel.
          %p I'm also, like, totally hireable right now, so feel free to <a href="mailto:zack@zackginies.com" title="Email me!">slide into those DMs</a>. But before you do, you should know that I excel on teams that value data, technology, humanity, empathy and diversity.

        .section__content
          %h3.h3 Some things I'm really good at

          %ul.list.list--icons
            %li.list__list-item.heart
              .list__list-item-icon
              %h6.h6.list__list-item-title User Experience
              %p User research & testing, journeys, IA, wireframes, prototypes and flows.
            %li.list__list-item.design
